explanation: The maximum XOR is achieved by having all bits set to 1 where possible. The given operation allows us to clear any bit in a number if it's set in x, effectively allowing us to make any number have any bit cleared if we choose the right x. Thus, we can achieve the maximum XOR by ORing all numbers together, as this gives us the union of all bits set across the numbers, and any bit not set in this result cannot be set in the XOR result. 
